Im scheduled for c-section this thurs morning. Due to high risk. Im not actually due till 30th though. Im starting to get abit nervous and aggitated now about it all. So it all happened so quickly in the end but that pregnancy flew by because i didnt have one problem up until i went into labour. This time its non stop problems so i just feel very nervous now.

7 years ago I had my first. Went 41+5 and never dilated even 1/2 a centimeter, had c-section.  Now I'm 35 weeks tomorrow and scheduled for csection May 23rd. 1st pregnancy was flawless except havingo to have c-section. This pregnancy has been tough. Gestational diabetes, a bacterial and yeast infection at same time, heartburn all of 1st trimester and 90% of 2nd trimester. I think I'm going earlier than May 23rd c-section
I'm at 100 days left.  My baby girl is on her July/August here we come.
